thread.title: Bethlehem Freedom football team enters Class 4A state football rankings
thread.title_full: Bethlehem Freedom football team enters Class 4A state football rankings - The Morning Call

author: Stephen Miller
title: Bethlehem Freedom football team enters Class 4A state football rankings
text:
The last unbeaten football team in the EPC South Division has jumped into the Patriot-News/Pennlive Class 4A state poll.
Freedom enters the rankings at No. 9 after spending much of the season listed as a team to watch. Woodland Hills, Pine-Richland, Central Dauphin, North Allegheny and Pittsburgh Central Catholic form the top 5 in 4A.
Parkland tumbled from No. 2 among the state’s 4A teams to a team to watch after losing to Liberty last week. Liberty’s win moved it into the teams to watch list in 4A.
District 11’s teams did not move in the Class 3A poll this week. Bethlehem Catholic, which has won five straight games since its season-opening loss to Liberty, continues to sit at No. 7. Lehighton held steady at No. 10 after moving to 6-0.
Defending state champion Archbishop Wood, Imhotep Charter, West Allegheny, Conneaut and Central Valley are the top five teams in this week’s 3A poll. Saucon Valley remains a 3A team to watch.
District 11 does not have a ranked team or a team to watch in the Class 2A and Class A polls.
